Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo registered a triple-double with 11 points, 12 rebounds, and a season-high 13 assists.
Damian Lillard added 25 points for the Bucks.
Antetokounmpo suffered a cut finger in the first half that required stitches but continued to play before being rested in the fourth quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Bucks coach Doc Rivers praised Antetokounmpo's performance, stating, 'He set the whole tone to our team. When your best player does that it becomes contagious and the ball just moved.'
